        <h2 class="section-title">Seixal at the Heart of Lisbon’s Next Growth Axis</h2>
        <p>The Parque Cidades do Tejo is one of the most ambitious metropolitan programs launched for Lisbon. Presented five months ago by Prime Minister Luís Montenegro—alongside the ministries of Finance, Territorial Cohesion, and Infrastructure & Housing—it signals a national mandate to transform the region into interconnected “sister cities” linked by the Tagus.</p>
        <p>A parity governance model between the Central Government and municipalities empowers the initiative to redefine planning, manage land reallocations, and direct infrastructure expansion while respecting environmental safeguards.</p>
        <div class="quick-facts">
          <div class="quick-fact">
            <strong>Regional Canvas</strong>
            <p>Spans the Arco Ribeirinho Sul (Almada, Barreiro, Seixal), the Ocean Campus in Oeiras, Lisbon’s Humberto Delgado Airport, and the future Luís de Camões Airport across Benavente and Montijo.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="quick-fact">
            <strong>Seixal’s Role</strong>
            <p>At the Portugal Real Estate Summit 2025, Lusoponte’s António Ramalho underscored the Arco Ribeirinho Sul—especially Seixal—as pivotal to unlocking the plan. Quinta do Palácio do Infante offers a ready-to-deploy asset within this priority hub.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="quick-fact">
            <strong>Investor Advantage</strong>
            <p>Our estate is more than land—it is a gateway into Lisbon’s state-backed growth axis, merging heritage, waterfront access, and strategic positioning in the metropolitan playbook.</p>
          </div>
