      <article class="card">
        <h3>Population Growth</h3>
        <p>Greater Lisbon added 120,000 residents in the past decade; Seixal captured 14% of that increase while housing pipeline lags by roughly 2,500 units.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Infrastructure Momentum</h3>
        <p>Upgrades to the Barreiro-Seixal ferry, expansion of the A33 corridor, and logistics hubs around the Port of Setúbal improve commuter convenience and freight movement.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Economic Expansion</h3>
        <p>Tech employers, nearshoring companies, and universities are establishing south bank footprints, bringing international talent and sustained rental demand.</p>
      </article>
